TITLE: Refactoring React Component to Use Hooks with Local Storage
DESCRIPTION: Refactoring the Counter component to use React Hooks (useState and useEffect) while maintaining localStorage integration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kentcdodds/kentcdodds.com/blob/main/content/blog/react-hooks-whats-going-to-happen-to-my-tests.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'

function Counter() {
	const [count, setCount] = useState(() =>
		Number(window.localStorage.getItem('count') || 0),
	)
	const incrementCount = () => setCount((c) => c + 1)
	useEffect(() => {
		window.localStorage.setItem('count', count)
	}, [count])
	return <button onClick={incrementCount}>{count}</button>
}

export default Counter
```

