TITLE: Array Method Chaining Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Uses chained array methods (map, filter, map) to process file paths and generate move commands. Takes a list of files from find command output, processes them, and generates shell commands for moving files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kentcdodds/kentcdodds.com/blob/main/content/blog/array-reduce-vs-chaining-vs-for-loop.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const lines = execSync(`find "${searchPath}" -type f`).toString().split('\n')

const commands = lines
	.map((f) => f.trim())
	.filter(Boolean)
	.map((file) => {
		const destFile = getDestFile(file)
		const destFileDir = path.dirname(destFile)
		return `mkdir -p "${destFileDir}" && mv "${file}" "${destFile}"`
	})

commands.forEach((command) => execSync(command))
```

