TITLE: Custom Array Filter Implementation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a basic implementation of a filter function that removes null and undefined values from an array, used as an example of when not to apply inversion of control.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kentcdodds/kentcdodds.com/blob/main/content/blog/inversion-of-control.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
function filter(array) {
	let newArray = []
	for (let index = 0; index < array.length; index++) {
		const element = array[index]
		if (element !== null && element !== undefined) {
			newArray[newArray.length] = element
		}
	}
	return newArray
}
```

