TITLE: Implementing Enum-like Types and Utility Functions in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This TypeScript code defines custom types for Team and Role, along with utility functions to check and handle these types. It's used to maintain enum-like functionality after migrating to SQLite, which doesn't support enums natively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kentcdodds/kentcdodds.com/blob/main/content/blog/i-migrated-from-a-postgres-cluster-to-distributed-sqlite-with-litefs.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
