TITLE: Custom listify function implementation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet provides a custom implementation of a listify function that creates human-readable lists from arrays.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kentcdodds/kentcdodds.com/blob/main/content/blog/listify-a-java-script-array.mdx#2025-04-12_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function listify(
	array,
	{ conjunction = 'and ', stringify = (item) => item.toString() } = {},
) {
	return array.reduce((list, item, index) => {
		if (index === 0) return stringify(item)
		if (index === array.length - 1) {
			if (index === 1) return `${list} ${conjunction}${stringify(item)}`
			else return `${list}, ${conjunction}${stringify(item)}`
		}
		return `${list}, ${stringify(item)}`
	}, '')
}
```

